Mxolisi Mngadi SA police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police are searching for more suspects for the murder
of 39-year-old police constable Ncedo Katoyi in Khayelitsha. One person has been arrested so far and Western
Cape police spokesperson Brigadier Novela Potelwa said that the police were
"still in pursuit of more suspects". According to Potelwa, a gang of six opened fire on
Katoyi and his partner as they made their way back to their vehicle in Site C,
Khayelitsha. They had responded to a complaint in Site C.
Katoyi's service pistol had been taken and he died at the scene. A 32-year-old man was arrested in connection with
Katoyi's murder on April 26, Captain Philani Nkwalase said. The man, Lwandile Wiseman
Somdaka, was arrested at midnight at his
residence in Ilitha Park, Khayelitsha. He appeared in the Khayelitsha Magistrate's Court
on April 30 and the case has been postponed to May 7 for further investigation,
Nkwalase added. Somdaka is in custody. "His arrest was a result of a rigorous manhunt
led by the Hawks' National Bureau for Illegal Firearms Control and Priority
Violent Crime Unit, which also involved Khayelitsha detectives and Vispol (SAPS
visible policing)," Nkwalase said in a statement . Anyone with information that could lead to more
arrests should contact the investigating officer on 082 302 7114.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  